        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 4:09PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 409 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles south of Kennedy Meadow, or 14 miles southwest of Sonora Pass,
moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern
Tuolumne County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
